To start a NodeJs application with TypeScript:
    1) Follow this article : https://basarat.gitbooks.io/typescript/docs/quick/nodejs.html.
		1- Edit tsconfig.json: include: ["./src/**/*"] to "./src/**/*".
		2- Edit package.json build:live index.ts accourding to your starting file directory.
    2) Run Nodemon and tsc -watch
    2) Now you can import builtin NodeJS modules like this: import * as os from "os".
    3) You can edit package.json script to change the location of the starting file.
    4) To use npm packages, use npm install @types/<package-name> and import as previously mentioned.
    5) you can use yargs library to have better parsing for command parameters.
    6)



